1. Quantum Computing Subsystem

1.1 Quantum Processing Unit (QPU) Specifications

1.1.1 Core QPU Architecture

```
Model: QE-1024 Quantum Energy Processor
Qubit Count: 1024 logical qubits
Qubit Type: Superconducting transmon qubits
Qubit Connectivity: All-to-all via quantum bus
Error Rate: 
  - Single-qubit gate: 99.999% fidelity
  - Two-qubit gate: 99.99% fidelity
  - Measurement: 99.9% fidelity
Coherence Times:
  - T1: 500 μs
  - T2: 300 μs
  - T2*: 400 μs
Gate Times:
  - Single-qubit: 20 ns
  - Two-qubit: 40 ns
  - Measurement: 1 μs
Error Correction: Surface-21 code (distance 21)
Logical Qubit Overhead: 49 physical qubits per logical qubit
Physical Qubit Count: 50,176
```

1.1.2 Cryogenic System

```
Refrigeration: Dilution refrigerator
Operating Temperature: 10 mK
Cooling Power: 1.5 W at 100 mK
Stages:
  - Stage 1: 50 K (pulse tube)
  - Stage 2: 4 K (He-4 sorption)
  - Stage 3: 1 K (He-3 sorption)
  - Stage 4: 10 mK (dilution)
Magnetic Shielding: 6-layer μ-metal + superconducting shield
Vibration Isolation: 3-stage active + passive isolation
```

1.1.3 Control Electronics

```
AWG Channels: 1024 (1 per qubit)
Sampling Rate: 10 GS/s
Bandwidth: 5 GHz
Resolution: 14 bits
Latency: < 5 ns
Power Consumption: 50 W per 16 channels
Communication: Optical fiber, 100 Gbps per link
```

1.1.4 Quantum Memory

```
Type: Microwave cavity memory
Capacity: 100 logical qubits
Storage Time: 100 ms
Fidelity: 99.99%
Access Time: 100 ns
Architecture: 3D integrated with QPU
```

1.2 Quantum Algorithms for Energy Optimization

