  - Execution Time: < 1 ms for continent-scale grid

Algorithm 2: Quantum Linear System Solver (HHL)
  - Purpose: Grid contingency analysis
  - Matrix Size: 2^20 × 2^20
  - Condition Number: κ ≤ 10^6
  - Speedup: Exponential vs classical

Algorithm 3: Quantum Monte Carlo
  - Purpose: Renewable generation forecasting
  - Samples: 10^9 samples in 1 second
  - Accuracy: 99.99% confidence intervals
```

