```
Algorithm 4: Quantum Neural Networks (QNN)
  - Architecture: 512 input, 256 hidden, 64 output qubits
  - Layers: 10 variational quantum layers
  - Training: Quantum natural gradient descent
  - Applications: Load forecasting, fault prediction

Algorithm 5: Quantum Support Vector Machine (QSVM)
  - Kernel: Quantum kernel estimation
  - Features: 2^20 dimensional feature space
  - Training Time: O(log N) vs O(N) classical
  - Applications: Anomaly detection, cyber attack classification
```

1.2.3 Simulation Algorithms

```
Algorithm 6: Quantum Chemistry for Battery Materials
  - System Size: 200+ atoms
  - Accuracy: Chemical accuracy (1 kcal/mol)
  - Applications: Novel battery material discovery

Algorithm 7: Quantum Plasma Physics
  - Purpose: Fusion plasma control
  - Particles: 10^6 particle simulations
