7. Communication Network Architecture

7.1 Multi-Layer Network Topology

7.1.1 Space Layer (Satellite)

```
LEO Constellation:
  - Satellites: 1000
  - Altitude: 550 km
  - Frequency: Ka-band (26-40 GHz)
  - Capacity: 1 Tbps per satellite
  - Latency: 20-40 ms
  - Coverage: Global, continuous

GEO Satellites:
  - Satellites: 24
  - Position: Geostationary orbit
  - Frequency: Q/V band (40-75 GHz)
  - Capacity: 500 Gbps per satellite
  - Latency: 240 ms
  - Purpose: Broadcast, quantum key distribution

Quantum Satellite Links:
  - Entanglement Distribution: 1000 km separation
  - Key Rate: 1 kbps secure key over 1000 km
  - Source: SPDC (Spontaneous Parametric Down-Conversion)
  - Detection: Superconducting nanowire single-photon detectors
```

7.1.2 Atmospheric Layer

```
5G/6G Networks:
  - Frequency: Sub-6 GHz + mmWave (24-71 GHz)
  - Bandwidth: 400 MHz aggregated
  - Latency: < 1 ms air interface
  - Reliability: 99.9999%
  - Mobility: Up to 500 km/h

Free-Space Optical:
  - Wavelength: 1550 nm
  - Data Rate: 100 Gbps per link
  - Range: 10 km (clear weather)
  - Beam Divergence: 0.1 mrad
  - Tracking: Micro-electromechanical (MEMS) mirrors
```

7.1.3 Terrestrial Layer

```
Fiber Optic Backbone:
  - Type: Single-mode, ultra-low loss
  - Loss: 0.15 dB/km @ 1550 nm
