```

7.2 Network Protocols Stack

7.2.1 Application Layer

```
EnergyOS Protocol Suite:
  - E-RPC: Remote procedure calls for energy control
    - Authentication: Quantum-resistant signatures
    - Encryption: AES-256-GCM with quantum key distribution
    - Latency: < 1 ms for critical commands
  - GridSync: Time synchronization protocol
    - Accuracy: ±10 ns across continent
    - Method: White rabbit protocol extension
  - EnergyStream: Real-time telemetry streaming
    - Format: Protocol buffers with schema evolution
    - Compression: Lossless, 10:1 typical ratio
    - Rate: 1 Mbps per major asset
```

7.2.2 Transport Layer

```
Reliable-UDP (RUDP):
  - Purpose: Sensor data, telemetry
  - Features: Selective ACK, congestion control
  - Loss Tolerance: < 0.1% packet loss
  - Jitter: < 1 ms

Quantum-Secure TCP (QS-TCP):
  - Encryption: Post-quantum TLS 1.3
  - Authentication: SPHINCS+ signatures
  - Key Exchange: Kyber KEM
  - Perfect Forward Secrecy: Yes
```

7.2.3 Network Layer

```
Energy IPv6 (E-IPv6):
  - Addressing: Hierarchical based on grid topology
  - Routing: Geographic + topological routing
  - Mobility: Seamless handover for mobile assets
  - Multicast: Efficient group communication for grid control

Delay/Disruption Tolerant Networking (DTN):
  - Store-and-Forward: For intermittent connectivity
  - Bundle Protocol: With energy-specific extensions
  - Priority: 8 priority levels for different message types
```

7.2.4 Link Layer

```
Time-Sensitive Networking (TSN):
  - Standards: IEEE 802.1Qbv, 802.1Qbu, 802.1Qci
  - Latency: < 10 μs guaranteed
  - Jitter: < 1 μs
  - Synchronization: IEEE 802.1AS with < 10 ns accuracy

Cognitive Radio:
  - Spectrum Sensing: Real-time across 100 MHz-6 GHz
  - Dynamic Spectrum Access: Without interfering primary users
  - MIMO: 8×8 MIMO for capacity and reliability
```

