8. Data Architecture & Processing Pipeline

8.1 Data Characteristics & Volume

8.1.1 Data Sources & Rates

```
Sensors (10 billion devices):
  - Smart Meters: 1 reading/second, 100 bytes = 1 TB/s global
  - Grid Sensors: 10k readings/second, 1 KB = 100 TB/s
  - Environmental: 1 reading/minute, 1 KB = 10 GB/s
  - Asset Monitoring: 100 readings/second, 10 KB = 10 TB/s
  - Total Raw Sensor Data: ~200 TB/second globally

Imagery & Video:
  - Satellite: 1 PB/day (100 satellites, 1 m resolution)
  - Drone: 100 TB/day (10,000 drones)
  - Fixed Cameras: 1 EB/day (100 million cameras)
  - Total Visual Data: ~1.1 EB/day

Acoustic & Vibration:
  - Substations: 1 GB/sec per site × 100k sites = 100 TB/s
  - Transmission Lines: 100 MB/sec per line × 1M km = 100 TB/s
  - Total Acoustic: ~200 TB/s

Total Ingest Rate: ~500 TB/second continuous
```

8.1.2 Data Types & Formats

```
Structured Data (20%):
  - Time-series: InfluxDB Line Protocol
  - Telemetry: Protocol Buffers (protobuf)
  - Transactions: Avro with schema registry
  - Configuration: YAML/JSON with validation

Unstructured Data (80%):
  - Images: JPEG2000 with metadata
  - Video: H.265 with temporal compression
  - Audio: FLAC for high fidelity, Opus for telemetry
  - Documents: PDF/A for archival

Semi-structured:
  - Logs: Common Log Format with structured fields
  - Traces: OpenTelemetry format
  - Events: CloudEvents specification
```

8.2 Storage Architecture

8.2.1 Storage Hierarchy

```
L0: Edge Cache (1 ms access)
  - Size: 1 TB per edge node
  - Technology: NVMe SSD
  - Purpose: Real-time processing buffer

L1: Regional Storage (10 ms access)
  - Size: 1 PB per region
  - Technology: All-flash array
  - Purpose: Recent data, hot analytics

L2: Continental Archive (100 ms access)
  - Size: 100 PB per continent
  - Technology: Hybrid flash/tape
  - Purpose: 1-year rolling archive

L3: Global Cold Storage (1 second access)
  - Size: 1 EB global
  - Technology: Tape libraries with robotic access
  - Purpose: 10-year+ archive, compliance

L4: Immutable Archive (10 second access)
  - Size: 10 EB global
  - Technology: DNA storage, quartz glass
  - Purpose: Permanent records, 100+ year retention
```

8.2.2 Database Systems

```
Time-Series Databases:
  - Primary: InfluxDB 3.0 (Rust rewrite)
  - Capacity: 1 trillion points per database
  - Compression: 10:1 average
  - Query Speed: 1 billion points/second scan
  - Retention: Automatic tiering to object storage

Graph Databases:
  - Primary: Neo4j for knowledge graphs
  - Scale: 1 trillion nodes, 10 trillion relationships
  - Traversal: Millisecond for 10-hop queries
  - Applications: Grid topology, dependency graphs

Document Stores:
  - Primary: MongoDB with sharding
  - Scale: 1 billion documents per collection
  - Indexes: Compound, geospatial, full-text
  - Consistency: Tunable from eventual to strong

Object Storage:
  - Primary: Ceph with erasure coding
  - Durability: 99.999999999% (11 nines)
  - Availability: 99.99%
  - Throughput: 100 Gbps per cluster
```

8.3 Processing Pipeline

8.3.1 Real-Time Processing (Sub-millisecond)

```
Framework: Apache Flink with custom extensions
Latency: < 1 ms event time
Throughput: 10 million events/second per node
State Management: RocksDB with SSD backing
Checkpointing: Asynchronous, every 10 ms
Applications: Grid stabilization, emergency response
```

8.3.2 Near-Real-Time Processing (Seconds)

```
Framework: Apache Spark Structured Streaming
Latency: 1 second micro-batches
Throughput: 1 billion records/second per cluster
State: Delta Lake for ACID transactions
Applications: Demand response, market clearing
```

8.3.3 Batch Processing (Hours)

```
Framework: Apache Spark + Dask
Scale: Exabyte-scale datasets
Optimization: Query planning with materialized views
Cost: $1 per TB processed
Applications: Long-term forecasting, asset optimization
```

8.3.4 Stream Processing Architecture

```
Ingestion Layer:
  - Apache Kafka: 10 million messages/second per cluster
  - Retention: 7 days hot, 30 days warm
  - Replication: 3x across availability zones
  - Compression: Zstandard with 5:1 ratio

Processing Layer:
  - Stateless: Kafka Streams for simple transformations
  - Stateful: Flink for complex event processing
  - Windowing: Tumbling, sliding, session windows
  - Watermarks: Event time with late data handling

Serving Layer:
  - Real-time: Apache Pinot for sub-second queries
  - Historical: Presto/Trino for interactive queries
  - APIs: GraphQL with real-time subscriptions
```

