9. Control Systems & Grid Intelligence

9.1 Grid Control Hierarchy

9.1.1 Primary Control (Millisecond)

```
Frequency Control:
  - Response Time: < 100 ms
  - Actuators: Battery storage, generator governors
  - Algorithm: Droop control with quantum optimization
  - Objective: Maintain 60.00 Hz ± 0.01 Hz

Voltage Control:
  - Response Time: < 50 ms
  - Actuators: STATCOM, SVC, capacitor banks
  - Algorithm: Model predictive control
  - Objective: Maintain voltage within ±0.5%
```

9.1.2 Secondary Control (Seconds)

```
Automatic Generation Control (AGC):
  - Cycle Time: 2-4 seconds
  - Objective: Balance generation and load
  - Algorithm: Economic dispatch with security constraints
  - Optimization: Quantum linear programming

Load Frequency Control:
  - Response: 30 seconds to settle
  - Reserves: Primary, secondary, tertiary
  - Coordination: Across balancing authorities
```

9.1.3 Tertiary Control (Minutes-Hours)

```
Economic Dispatch:
  - Interval: 5 minutes
  - Objective: Minimize cost while meeting demand
  - Constraints: Transmission limits, generator limits
  - Solution: Mixed-integer linear programming

Unit Commitment:
  - Horizon: 24-48 hours
  - Decision: Which generators to start/stop
  - Complexity: NP-hard, solved with quantum annealing
  - Uncertainty: Stochastic optimization for renewables
```

9.2 Protection Systems

9.2.1 Digital Protective Relays

```
Sampling Rate: 10 kHz (160 samples/cycle @ 60 Hz)
Decision Time: < 1 cycle (16.67 ms)
Algorithms: 
  - Differential protection: 87L, 87T
  - Distance protection: 21
  - Overcurrent: 50, 51
  - Directional: 67
Communication: IEC 61850-9-2 Sampled Values
Security: Cryptographic authentication of all commands
```

9.2.2 Wide-Area Protection

```
System Integrity Protection Schemes (SIPS):
  - Response Time: < 100 ms for system-wide events
  - Measurements: PMU data from 1000+ locations
  - Decisions: Remedial action schemes
  - Coordination: Across utility boundaries

Special Protection Schemes:
  - Underfrequency Load Shedding (UFLS)
  - Undervoltage Load Shedding (UVLS)
  - System Separation Schemes
  - Generator Tripping Schemes
```

9.3 Energy Management System (EMS)

9.3.1 SCADA System

```
Data Acquisition:
  - Scan Rate: 1 second for critical, 5 seconds for normal
  - Points: 10 million+ per control area
  - Protocols: DNP3, IEC 60870-5-104, Modbus
  - Redundancy: Hot-standby with 100 ms failover

Human-Machine Interface (HMI):
  - Refresh Rate: 1 second
  - Displays: 1000+ with hierarchical navigation
  - Alarm Management: Intelligent filtering and prioritization
  - Visualization: 3D grid representation with AR overlay
```

9.3.2 Advanced Applications

```
State Estimation:
  - Frequency: Every 1 minute
  - Measurements: SCADA + PMU (mixed measurement)
  - Algorithm: Weighted least squares with bad data detection
  - Accuracy: Voltage magnitude ±0.1%, angle ±0.1°

Contingency Analysis:
  - Scope: N-1, N-1-1, N-2 contingencies
  - Number: 10,000+ contingencies analyzed
  - Time: < 5 minutes for full analysis
  - Action: Preventive and corrective actions identified

Optimal Power Flow (OPF):
  - Variables: 100,000+ (generation, voltage, phase shifters)
  - Constraints: 1 million+ (thermal, voltage, stability)
  - Solution: Interior point method with warm start
  - Frequency: Every 5 minutes
```

9.4 Market Systems

9.4.1 Real-Time Market

```
Clearing Interval: 5 minutes
Participants: 1000+ generators, 100+ load serving entities
Products: Energy, regulation, spinning reserve
Clearing: Security-constrained economic dispatch
Settlement: Financial settlement every 15 minutes
