10. Security Architecture

10.1 Cybersecurity Framework

10.1.1 Zero Trust Architecture

```
Perimeter: No implicit trust based on network location
Authentication: Multi-factor for all access attempts
Authorization: Attribute-based access control (ABAC)
Microsegmentation: Each device in its own segment
Continuous Verification: Session re-validation every 5 minutes
```

10.1.2 Network Security

```
Firewalls: Next-generation with deep packet inspection
  - Throughput: 100 Gbps per device
  - Rules: 100,000+ with hierarchical organization
  - Inspection: SSL/TLS decryption at line rate

Intrusion Prevention Systems (IPS):
  - Detection Methods: Signature, anomaly, behavior-based
  - False Positive Rate: < 0.1%
  - Throughput: 40 Gbps per sensor
  - Response: Automated blocking with human confirmation

Network Segmentation:
  - OT Network: Isolated from IT with one-way data diodes
  - Control Network: Separate VLANs for different criticality
  - Management Network: Dedicated out-of-band management
```

10.2 Cryptography & Key Management

10.2.1 Post-Quantum Cryptography

```
Algorithms:
  - Key Exchange: Kyber (NIST selected)
  - Signatures: Dilithium (NIST selected)
  - Hash-based: SPHINCS+ (NIST selected)
  - Code-based: Classic McEliece (NIST selected)

Implementation:
  - Libraries: Open Quantum Safe (liboqs)
  - Performance: < 10 ms for key exchange
  - Key Sizes: 2-10 KB depending on security level
  - Compatibility: Hybrid mode with classical crypto
```

10.2.2 Quantum Key Distribution

```
QKD Systems:
  - Type: Prepare-and-measure with decoy states
  - Distance: 100 km over fiber, 10 km free-space
  - Key Rate: 10 Mbps at 10 km, 1 kbps at 100 km
  - Integration: With IPsec, MACsec for network encryption

Key Management:
  - Centralized: For policy management
  - Distributed: For resilience
  - Storage: Hardware security modules (HSM)
  - Lifecycle: Automated key rotation every 24 hours
```

10.2.3 Hardware Security Modules

```
Certifications: FIPS 140-3 Level 4
Performance: 10,000 RSA-2048 signs/second
Capacity: 100,000 keys per device
Availability: Clustered with automatic failover
Management: Role-based with separation of duties
```

10.3 Physical Security

10.3.1 Critical Facility Protection

```
Access Control:
  - Biometrics: Multimodal (face, iris, fingerprint)
  - Badging: Smart cards with PKI certificates
  - Authorization: Time-based, location-based rules
  - Audit: Complete log of all access attempts

Surveillance:
  - Cameras: 4K with AI-based analytics
  - Coverage: 100% with no blind spots
  - Retention: 90 days continuous, 7 years for events
  - Analytics: Behavior analysis, object detection

Perimeter Security:
  - Fencing: 3-meter with vibration sensors
  - Lighting: LED with motion activation
  - Intrusion Detection: Microwave, infrared, fence sensors
  - Response: Security personnel within 2 minutes
```

10.3.2 Tamper Protection

```
Enclosures: TEMPEST-rated for electromagnetic protection
Seals: Tamper-evident with cryptographic verification
Sensors: Vibration, temperature, light, position
Response: Automatic zeroization of keys upon tamper detection
```

10.4 Security Operations Center (SOC)

10.4.1 Monitoring & Detection

```
Security Information and Event Management (SIEM):
  - Events: 1 million events/second ingestion
  - Retention: 7 years for compliance
  - Correlation: Real-time across all data sources
  - Analytics: Machine learning for anomaly detection

Threat Intelligence:
  - Feeds: 50+ commercial and open-source feeds
  - Integration: Automated IOC ingestion and matching
  - Analysis: Human analysts + AI for pattern recognition
  - Sharing: ISACs (Information Sharing and Analysis Centers)
```

10.4.2 Incident Response

```
Playbooks: 100+ automated response playbooks
Orchestration: SOAR platform for automation
Containment: Network isolation within 30 seconds
Forensics: Complete timeline reconstruction
Recovery: Automated restoration from known good state
```

10.4.3 Vulnerability Management

```
Scanning: Continuous vulnerability assessment
Prioritization: CVSS + asset criticality + exploit availability
Remediation: Automated patching for non-critical systems
Validation: Verification of patch effectiveness
```

