11. Environmental Monitoring Systems

11.1 Atmospheric Monitoring

11.1.1 Air Quality Sensors

```
Parameters:
  - Particulate Matter: PM1, PM2.5, PM10
  - Gases: O₃, NO₂, SO₂, CO
  - Greenhouse Gases: CO₂, CH₄, N₂O
  - Meteorological: Temperature, humidity, pressure, wind

Accuracy:
  - CO₂: ±1 ppm or ±1% of reading
  - PM2.5: ±1 μg/m³ or ±5% of reading
  - NO₂: ±1 ppb or ±5% of reading

Spatial Density: 1 sensor per 1 km² in urban areas
Data Rate: 1 sample/minute
Communication: LoRaWAN for low power, 5G for high bandwidth
```

11.1.2 Weather Monitoring

```
Doppler Radar:
  - Range: 250 km
  - Resolution: 250 m range, 1° azimuth
  - Update: Every 5 minutes
  - Products: Reflectivity, velocity, spectrum width

Weather Satellites:
  - Geostationary: 5-minute updates, 1 km resolution
  - Polar Orbiting: 2× daily, 500 m resolution
  - Microwave: Cloud penetration, precipitation estimation

Weather Stations:
  - Network: 10,000+ stations
  - Parameters: Temperature, humidity, pressure, wind, precipitation
  - Accuracy: Temperature ±0.1°C, wind speed ±0.1 m/s
```

11.2 Terrestrial Monitoring

11.2.1 Seismic Monitoring

```
Seismometers:
  - Type: Broadband with 24-bit digitizer
  - Bandwidth: 0.01 Hz to 100 Hz
  - Dynamic Range: > 140 dB
  - Network: 1000+ stations, 10 km spacing in fault zones

Early Warning:
  - Detection Time: < 5 seconds after earthquake initiation
  - Alert Time: Up to 60 seconds before shaking arrives
  - Accuracy: Magnitude ±0.2, location ±2 km
  - Actions: Automatic shutdown of sensitive equipment
```

11.2.2 Soil & Groundwater Monitoring

```
Soil Sensors:
  - Moisture: 0-100% volumetric water content, ±1% accuracy
  - Temperature: -40°C to 85°C, ±0.1°C accuracy
  - Salinity: 0-20 dS/m, ±2% accuracy
  - Depth: Surface to 2 meters at multiple depths

Groundwater:
  - Level: Pressure transducers, ±1 cm accuracy
  - Quality: Multiparameter sondes for pH, conductivity, dissolved oxygen
  - Network: 100,000+ monitoring wells
```

11.3 Ocean Monitoring

11.3.1 Oceanographic Buoys

```
Parameters:
  - Surface: Temperature, salinity, waves, currents
  - Subsurface: Temperature profiles to 2000 m depth
  - Meteorological: Wind, air temperature, humidity, pressure
  - Biogeochemical: Chlorophyll, oxygen, pH, nutrients

Accuracy:
  - Temperature: ±0.001°C
  - Salinity: ±0.002 PSU
  - Waves: ±1 cm significant wave height
  - Currents: ±0.5 cm/s speed, ±2° direction

Deployment:
  - Moored buoys: 3000+ globally
  - Drifting buoys: 10,000+ Argo floats
  - Update Rate: Hourly for surface, 10-day profiles for subsurface
```

11.3.2 Sea Level Monitoring

```
Tide Gauges:
  - Type: Radar, acoustic, pressure
  - Accuracy: ±1 mm absolute, ±0.1 mm relative
  - Sampling: 1 minute intervals
  - Network: 2000+ gauges globally

Satellite Altimetry:
  - Satellites: Jason-3, Sentinel-6
  - Accuracy: ±2 cm absolute sea level
  - Resolution: 7 km along track, 1 Hz sampling
  - Coverage: Global every 10 days
```

