12.3 Transmission Line Design

12.3.1 Overhead Lines

```
Conductors: High-temperature low-sag (HTLS)
  - Types: ACCC, ACSS, GZTACSR
  - Capacity: Up to 3000 A per circuit
  - Sag: 30% less than conventional at high temperature

Towers: Lattice or tubular steel
  - Height: 30-100 meters depending on voltage
  - Foundation: Concrete caissons or piles
  - Design: For 100-year wind, ice loading

Insulators: Composite silicone rubber
  - Advantages: Lightweight, hydrophobic, vandal resistant
  - Maintenance: 50+ years without washing

Right-of-Way: 
  - Width: 60-200 meters depending on voltage
  - Vegetation Management: Automated with drones
  - Monitoring: Corridor surveillance with satellites
```

