14. Integration Interfaces & Protocols

14.1 Industry Standards Compliance

14.1.1 IEC Standards

```
IEC 61850: Communication networks and systems for power utility automation
  - Substation: IEC 61850-7-420 for DER
  - Hydro: IEC 61850-7-410 for hydropower
  - Process Bus: IEC 61850-9-2 for sampled values

IEC 61970/61968: Common Information Model (CIM)
  - Modeling: Equipment, topology, measurements
  - Exchange: CIM/XML for data exchange
  - Extensions: For markets, planning, operations

IEC 60870: Telecontrol protocols
  - IEC 60870-5-101/104: For SCADA communication
  - IEC 60870-5-103: For protection equipment

IEC 62351: Security for IEC protocols
  - Authentication: Digital certificates for devices
  - Encryption: TLS for communication
  - Role-Based Access Control: For operations
```

14.1.2 IEEE Standards

```
IEEE 1547: Interconnection and interoperability of DER
  - Voltage and frequency ride-through
  - Power quality requirements
  - Communication and control

IEEE 2030.5: Smart Energy Profile 2.0
  - RESTful API for energy management
  - Security: TLS with certificate-based authentication
  - Functions: Demand response, pricing, metering

IEEE C37.118: Synchrophasor standards
  - Measurement: Phasor measurement units (PMUs)
  - Communication: Real-time streaming of measurements
  - Accuracy: Timing synchronized to GPS
```

14.1.3 Other Standards

```
DNP3: Distributed Network Protocol
  - Secure Authentication Version 5
  - Object models for common power system devices
  - Widely deployed in North America

Modbus: Simple, widely adopted protocol
  - Modbus TCP for Ethernet networks
  - Modbus RTU for serial communication
  - Extensions for security and additional functions

OpenADR: Open Automated Demand Response
  - Signals: Price, reliability, emergency
  - Communication: Push and pull models
  - Participants: Utilities, aggregators, customers
```

14.2 API Specifications

14.2.1 REST APIs

```
Base URL: https://api.energos.earth/v1
Authentication: OAuth 2.0 with JWT tokens
Rate Limiting: Tiered based on subscription level
Versioning: Semantic versioning with deprecation notices
Documentation: OpenAPI 3.0 with interactive sandbox

Key Endpoints:
  - /grid/state: Real-time grid state
  - /market/prices: Energy market prices
  - /devices/{id}/control: Device control
  - /forecasts/{type}: Various forecasts
  - /alerts: Real-time alerts and notifications
```

14.2.2 Streaming APIs

```
Protocol: WebSocket with JSON messages
Authentication: Same as REST API
Reconnection: Automatic with exponential backoff
Compression: Per-message deflate compression
Guarantees: At-least-once delivery with sequence numbers

Streams:
  - /stream/grid/telemetry: Real-time telemetry
  - /stream/market/trades: Market trade stream
  - /stream/alerts: Real-time alert stream
  - /stream/events: System events stream
```

14.2.3 GraphQL API

```
Endpoint: https://api.energos.earth/graphql
Schema: Strongly typed with energy-specific types
Batching: Automatic query batching
Caching: Built-in caching with cache control
Real-time: Subscriptions for real-time updates

Example Query:
  query {
    grid(region: "CAISO") {
      frequency
      voltage(level: "transmission")
      load
      generationByType
    }
  }
```

14.3 Data Exchange Formats

14.3.1 Time-Series Data

```
Format: Apache Parquet with energy-specific schema
Compression: Zstandard with dictionary encoding
Partitioning: By time (hourly) and region
Metadata: Comprehensive metadata including quality flags
Performance: Columnar storage for efficient queries
```

14.3.2 Geospatial Data

```
Format: GeoJSON with energy extensions
Projection: WGS84 (EPSG:4326) for global, UTM for regional
Precision: 6 decimal degrees (~10 cm at equator)
Attributes: Comprehensive feature attributes
Topology: Preserved for network analysis
```

14.3.3 Market Data

```
Format: FIX/FAST for high-speed market data
Compression: Field encoding for efficiency
Latency: < 1 ms for market data dissemination
Reliability: Guaranteed delivery with sequence gaps
Synchronization: Nanosecond timestamps
```

